# Advanced Debugger

Minimalist, colorful, configurable debug logger for Python.

## Why Advanced Debugger?

- üë®‚Äçüíª Simple console logging of actions.
- üïê Debug with time specifying for one minute
- üóÑÔ∏è Takes only few lines for much debugs.

## Examples

Define debug category:
dbgVar = AdvDEBUG.define('title of your debug')

Print something:
dbgVar.info('Text to debug!')
OR
dbgVar('Text to debug!')

Available types:
	`WARN`
	`INFO`
	`ERROR`

Returns:
[title of your debug at DATE AND TIME] Text to debug!

Configure existing category:
dbgVar.cfg(title='REQUEST')

BEFORE: title of your debug
AFTER: REQUEST

## Change Log: v0.1.8

- Hot-fix of 0.1.7
- Added file logging feature
- Added new style "Minimalist"

